Phase 5 Task 1: Implement post_run_hook.gd

Implementation:
- Created spike/addons/gd-tools-coverage/post_run_hook.gd
- extends RefCounted, GUT post-run hook for coverage data serialization
- _init(): Gets tracker via _get_tracker(), checks is_active(), reads output path
  from GD_TOOLS_COVERAGE_OUTPUT env var (default: user://coverage.json),
  gets hits from tracker.get_hits(), builds JSON with version/timestamp/hits,
  writes to file via FileAccess
- _get_tracker(): Gets Engine.get_main_loop() as SceneTree, returns
  tree.root.get_node_or_null("_GDTCoverage")
- Timestamp: Time.get_datetime_string_from_system(true, false) + "Z" for ISO 8601 UTC

Design decisions:
- Uses Node return type for _get_tracker() since tracker extends Node
- is_active() check ensures silent no-op when coverage not active
- JSON.stringify with 2-space indent for readability

